cnetPlot

Source: R/cnetPlot.R
cnetPlot.Rd

The cnetPlot function generates a highly customizable concept network (CNET) visualization for gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA) results. It displays the relationships between enriched pathways and their associated genes as a network graph, where nodes represent pathways or genes and edges represent their associations. Users can control node and edge aesthetics, highlight specific pathways, and optionally map gene-level correlation values to node colors.

Usage

cnetPlot(
  seDataFgsea,
  showCategory = 5,
  nodeLabel = "category",
  fontSize = 1,
  color = NULL,
  circular = FALSE,
  breaklineN = 30,
  layout = igraph::layout_nicely,
  colorCategory = "#E5C494",
  sizeCategory = 0.9,
  colorItem = "#B3B3B3",
  sizeItem = 0.8,
  colorEdge = "grey80",
  sizeEdge = 0.4,
  hilight = "none",
  hilightAlpha = 0.3,
  seed = NULL
)

Arguments

seDataFgsea

A SummarizedExperiment object containing GSEA results. The object must include:

  • metadata(seDataFgsea)$gseaResult: A GSEA result object with pathway information, gene sets, and enrichment statistics.

  • (Optional) metadata(seDataFgsea)$cor.df: A data frame of gene-level correlation values, required when using the color parameter.

showCategory

Either a numeric value specifying the number of top pathways to display, or a character vector specifying specific pathway names. Default is 5.

nodeLabel

Character string specifying which type of nodes should be labeled. Must be one of c("category", "all", "none", "item", "gene", "exclusive", "share"). Default is "category".

fontSize

Numeric. Base size for text labels (applied as a scaling factor). Default is 1.

color

Character or NULL. The column name from metadata(seDataFgsea)$cor.df to be used for coloring gene nodes (e.g., correlation coefficients or log2 fold changes). When NULL, nodes are colored using the default item color. Default is NULL.

circular

Logical. Whether to arrange nodes in a circular layout. Default is FALSE.

breaklineN

Integer. Maximum number of characters before inserting line breaks in pathway names for improved readability. Default is 30.

layout

Layout function for node positioning. Default is igraph::layout_nicely. Can be replaced with any igraph layout function.

colorCategory

Character. Color for category (pathway) nodes. Default is "#E5C494".

sizeCategory

Numeric. Scaling factor for category node sizes. Default is 0.9.

colorItem

Character. Color for item (gene) nodes when color = NULL. Default is "#B3B3B3".

sizeItem

Numeric. Scaling factor for item (gene) node sizes. Default is 0.8.

colorEdge

Character. Edge color or "category" to color edges by their associated pathway. Default is "grey80".

sizeEdge

Numeric. Edge line width. Default is 0.4.

hilight

Character vector or "none". Pathways to highlight (opacity = 1). Non-highlighted nodes will have reduced opacity controlled by hilightAlpha. Default is "none".

hilightAlpha

Numeric. Transparency level (0–1) for non-highlighted nodes. Default is 0.3.

seed

Integer or NULL. Random seed for reproducible layout generation. Default is NULL.

Value

A named list containing three components:

  • cnetPlot: A ggplot2 object representing the concept network visualization.

  • tableEdgeCnetPlot: A data.frame of network edges with columns:

    • from: Pathway (category) identifier.

    • to: Gene symbol(s) associated with the pathway.

  • tableNodeCnetPlot: A data.frame of node attributes with columns:

    • id: Node identifier (pathway or gene name).

    • size: Node size used in visualization.

    • (Optional) Column named by color parameter, containing the numeric values mapped to gene color scale.

Details

This function builds upon ggtangle and igraph for flexible concept network visualization. Users can:

  • Control node/edge colors, sizes, and layout.

  • Overlay continuous gene metrics (e.g., correlation, fold change).

  • Highlight specific pathways using hilight.

  • Automatically wrap long pathway names using breaklineN.

When color is provided, gene nodes are colored according to their corresponding values using a diverging or sequential color scale. When color = NULL, all item nodes are rendered in a uniform grey tone.

Note

Requires ggtangle (>= 1.0.0), enrichplot (>= 1.21.0), and ggplot2 (>= 3.5.0) for full compatibility.

Examples

data("sig2Fun_result")
cnetPlot(seDataFgsea = sig2Fun_result,
         color = "cor")
